      <p>These carnivorous fish are aggressive and liable to make unprovoked attacks against anything that approaches them. Smaller <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">sharks</a> are from 5 to 8 feet long and not usually dangerous to creatures other than their prey. Large <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">sharks</a> can reach around 15 feet in length and are a serious threat. Huge <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">sharks</a> are true monsters, like great whites, that can exceed 20 feet in length.</p>
