        <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals141"/>
        <p><a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">Sharks</a> circle and observe potential prey, then dart in and bite with their powerful jaws.</p>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2312109"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals142"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Blindsense (Ex):</strong></span> A <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">shark</a> can locate creatures underwater within a 30-foot radius. This ability works only when the <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">shark</a> is underwater.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2312159"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals143"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Keen Scent (Ex):</strong></span> A <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">shark</a> can notice creatures by scent in a 180-foot radius and detect blood in the water at ranges of up to a mile.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="simplesect" lang="en">
          <div class="titlepage"/>
          <a name="id2312197"/>
          <div class="keywordset" style="display:none">
            <div class="keyword">other</div>
          </div>
          <a class="indexterm" name="MonstersAnimals144"/>
          <p><span class="strong"><strong>Skills:</strong></span> A <a href="ch73s39.html#MonstersAnimals140">shark</a> has a +8 racial bonus on any <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills311">Swim</a> check to perform some special action or avoid a hazard. It can always choose to take 10 on a <a href="ch16s03.html#CombinedSkills311">Swim</a> check, even if distracted or endangered. It can use the run action while swimming, provided it swims in a straight line.</p>
